+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jshb15cPUCGXCmvjswm8tw","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have now read all the files you requested. Here's a comprehensive report of the entire codebase:\n\n## Complete Codebase Analysis\n\n### 1. Project Overview\n\n**Name:** bench-fts-search (Full-text search feature benchmark)  \n**Type:** TypeScript/Node.js + Express + SQLite  \n**Purpose:** Add SQLite FTS5 (Full-Text Search) capabilities to an existing notes API\n\n---\n\n### 2. Package.json Dependencies\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-fts-search\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Full-text search feature benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"seed\": \"tsx src/seed.ts\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\",\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.0\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Database Setup (src/db.ts)\n\nCreates SQLite database with:\n- **Notes table structure:**\n  - `id` (INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT)\n  - `title` (TEXT NOT NULL)\n  - `body` (TEXT NOT NULL)\n  - `tags` (TEXT DEFAULT '[]' - JSON array as string)\n  - `created_at` (TEXT with datetime default)\n  - `updated_at` (TEXT with datetime default)\n\n- **Database configuration:**\n  - WAL journal mode for better concurrency\n  - Foreign keys enabled\n  - In-memory or file-based database support\n\n- **Seeding:** Includes 42 sample notes covering programming, cooking, travel, music, science, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Models (src/models.ts)\n\n```typescript\ninterface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string;  // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\ninterface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n}\n\ninterface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;  // with <mark> highlighting\n  rank: number;\n}\n\ninterface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Routes (src/routes.ts)\n\n**CRUD Endpoints:**\n\n1. **GET /notes** - List all notes with optional tag filtering\n   - Query: `?tag=<tagname>` filters by tag\n   - Response: `{ notes: Note[] }`\n\n2. **GET /notes/:id** - Get single note by ID\n   - Response: `{ note: Note }`\n   - Returns 404 if not found\n\n3. **POST /notes** - Create new note\n   - Validation: title and body required (non-empty)\n   - Input: `{ title, body, tags?: string[] }`\n   - Response: `{ note: Note }` (status 201)\n\n4. **PUT /notes/:id** - Update note (partial updates allowed)\n   - Input: `{ title?, body?, tags?: string[] }`\n   - Response: `{ note: Note }`\n   - Returns 404 if not found\n   - Updates `updated_at` timestamp\n\n5. **DELETE /notes/:id** - Delete note\n   - Response: 204 No Content\n   - Returns 404 if not found\n\n**Tag filtering:** Uses `json_each` to query JSON arrays in SQLite\n\n---\n\n### 6. Error Handling (src/errors.ts)\n\nTwo custom error classes:\n\n```typescript\nclass NotFoundError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 404;\n}\n\nclass ValidationError extends Error {\n  statusCode = 400;\n}\n\n// Middleware for global error handling\nfunction errorHandler(err: Error, req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction)\n```\n\nHandles:\n- NotFoundError → 404 with error message\n- ValidationError → 400 with error message\n- Other errors → 500 Internal Server Error\n\n---\n\n### 7. Server Setup (src/server.ts)\n\n```typescript\nexport function createApp(dbPath?: string): App {\n  // Creates Express app with:\n  // - JSON middleware\n  // - CRUD routes\n  // - Error handler middleware\n  // Returns { app, db }\n}\n\nexport function createSeededApp(dbPath?: string): App {\n  // Creates app and seeds database\n  // Returns { app, db }\n}\n```\n\n**Main startup:** Listens on port 3000 (or PORT env var) when run directly\n\n---\n\n### 8. Seed Script (src/seed.ts)\n\nStandalone script that:\n- Creates database at path specified in args or `notes.db`\n- Inserts 42 sample notes from `getSeedNotes()` array\n- Logs success with count of seeded notes\n- Closes database after completion\n\n**Sample notes include:**\n- Programming topics (TypeScript, Python, React, Docker, Kubernetes, Rust, etc.)\n- Cooking/Food (Pasta, Cookies, Coffee, Thai, French cuisine)\n- Travel (Tokyo, Paris, Kilimanjaro, Appalachian Trail)\n- Science (Quantum Computing, Solar System, Neural Networks)\n- Music (Jazz History, Guitar, Classical Music)\n- Health/Wellness (Yoga, Meditation, Sleep Science, Diet)\n- And many more across 12+ categories\n\n---\n\n### 9. Existing CRUD Tests (tests/notes.test.ts)\n\n**15 test cases covering:**\n\n1. GET /notes returns all notes\n2. GET /notes/:id returns specific note\n3. GET /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n4. POST /notes creates note with title and body\n5. POST /notes creates note with tags\n6. POST /notes returns 400 without title\n7. POST /notes returns 400 without body\n8. PUT /notes/:id updates note\n9. PUT /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n10. DELETE /notes/:id removes note\n11. DELETE /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n12. GET /notes?tag=X filters by tag\n13. Notes have created_at timestamp\n14. Notes have updated_at timestamp\n15. PUT updates updated_at timestamp\n\nAll use in-memory database (`:memory:`) and supertest HTTP testing\n\n---\n\n### 10. Search Tests (tests/search.test.ts)\n\n**20 test cases requiring implementation:**\n\n**Search Endpoint Tests (1-10):**\n1. GET /notes/search?q=keyword returns matching notes\n2. Results have snippet field\n3. Snippets contain `<mark>` tags around matched terms\n4. Results ranked by relevance (ascending rank order = most relevant)\n5. Supports exact phrase queries with quotes\n6. Returns id, title, snippet, rank fields\n7. Non-existent search returns empty array\n8. Missing q parameter returns 400\n9. Empty q parameter returns 400\n10. Pagination with page=1 returns up to 20 results\n\n**Pagination Tests (10-12):**\n10. page=1 returns first 20 results\n11. page=2 returns next batch\n12. Response includes total count\n\n**Suggest Endpoint Tests (13-15):**\n13. GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix returns up to 5 titles\n14. Suggest results match prefix in title\n15. Empty q parameter returns 400\n\n**Sync Tests (16-18):**\n16. FTS syncs on create - new note appears in search\n17. FTS syncs on update - updated content searchable, old content removed\n18. FTS syncs on delete - deleted note disappears from search\n\n**Robustness Tests (19-20):**\n19. Special characters in query don't crash\n20. Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset\n\n---\n\n### 11. Task Requirements (TASK.md)\n\n**Timeout:** 30 minutes\n\n**Requirements to implement:**\n\n1. **Search Endpoint: GET /notes/search?q=<query>**\n   - FTS5 across title and body\n   - BM25 ranking\n   - `<mark>` snippet highlighting\n   - Quoted phrase support\n   - 20 results per page with pagination\n   - Response: `{ results: SearchResult[], total: number, page: number, perPage: number }`\n   - Returns 400 if q missing/empty\n\n2. **Suggest Endpoint: GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>**\n   - Up to 5 matching titles\n   - Prefix matching on title and body\n   - Response: `{ results: SuggestResult[] }`\n   - Returns 400 if q missing/empty\n\n3. **FTS Index Sync**\n   - Must stay in sync with CRUD operations\n   - Can use triggers or manual sync\n\n---\n\n### 12. Configuration Files\n\n**tsconfig.json:**\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Source maps and declarations\n\n**vitest.config.ts:**\n- Global test utilities\n- 10 second test timeout\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a full-text search implementation task for a Node.js/Express/SQLite notes API. The codebase already has:\n- Complete CRUD API for notes with tag filtering\n- 42 seeded sample notes\n- 15 passing CRUD tests\n- 20 search tests waiting to be implemented\n\n**What needs to be built:**\n- SQLite FTS5 virtual table for indexing\n- Search endpoint with BM25 ranking and snippet generation\n- Suggest/autocomplete endpoint\n- Trigger or manual sync mechanism to keep FTS in sync with CRUD operations\n- All code must pass both existing CRUD tests and new search tests"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae95671 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 31486\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 25833</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c18d800-2cdb-489d-a728-8a60b4072b0f","uuid":"c1bb888b-ed9a-475a-8743-6b383e62470c","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The overall project structure (all files)\n2. The database setup in src/db.ts\n3. The models in src/models.ts\n4. The routes in src/routes.ts\n5. The error handling in src/errors.ts\n6. The server setup in src/server.ts\n7. The seed script in src/seed.ts\n8. The existing tests in tests/notes.test.ts\n9. The search tests in tests/search.test.ts\n10. The package.json for dependencies and scripts\n\nRead ALL of these files completely and report their full contents back to me.","agentId":"ae95671","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have now read all the files you requested. Here's a comprehensive report of the entire codebase:\n\n## Complete Codebase Analysis\n\n### 1. Project Overview\n\n**Name:** bench-fts-search (Full-text search feature benchmark)  \n**Type:** TypeScript/Node.js + Express + SQLite  \n**Purpose:** Add SQLite FTS5 (Full-Text Search) capabilit